Class PacketUtils

public class PacketUtils

WRITE_PACKETS

public static PacketList WRITE_PACKETS(RegisterType register,
                                       java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> data)
                                throws BitstreamException
Create the necessary packets for writing data. If the data can fit in a single type 1 packet (less than Packet.MAX_TYPE_ONE_SIZE), a single type one write packet will be created. If it is too large to fit in a type 1 packet but small enough for a type 2 packet, a zero word type 1 packet followed by a type 2 packet will be created. If there are too many words for a type 2 packet, an exception will be thrown.

Parameters:
data - The data to write into the packets.
Returns:
The resulting packet list.
Throws:
BitstreamException
